ğŸ”¨ What did I build?
A custom Linked List class in JavaScript with:

âœ… prepend() - Add a node at the beginning

âœ… append() - Add a node at the end

âœ… Utility methods like isEmpty(), getSize(), and print()

ğŸ’» Code Snapshot
js
Copy
Edit
class Node {
  constructor(value) {
    this.value = value;
    this.next = null;
  }
}

class LinkedList {
  constructor() {
    this.head = null;
    this.size = 0;
  }

  isEmpty() {
    return this.size === 0;
  }

  getSize() {
    return this.size;
  }

  prepend(value) {
    const node = new Node(value);
    node.next = this.head;
    this.head = node;
    this.size++;
  }

  append(value) {
    const node = new Node(value);
    if (this.isEmpty()) {
      this.head = node;
    } else {
      let prev = this.head;
      while (prev.next) {
        prev = prev.next;
      }
      prev.next = node;
    }
    this.size++;
  }

  print() {
    let current = this.head;
    while (current) {
      console.log(current.value);
      current = current.next;
    }
  }
}

// Usage
const list = new LinkedList();
list.prepend(10);
list.prepend(20);
list.append(40);
list.append(50);
list.print();
â± Time Complexity

Operation	Time Complexity
prepend()	O(1)
append()	O(n)
print()	O(n)
âœ… prepend is lightning fast.
âš ï¸ append traverses the list â€” can be improved using a tail pointer!

